      "title": {
        "en": "A Medieval Maritime Village",
        "de": "Was Vernazza besonders macht",
        "fr": "Ce qui rend Vernazza spécial",
        "it": "Un Porto da Sogno"
      },
      "subtitle": {
        "en": "Once a thriving maritime power, Vernazza retains its authentic character."
      },
      "content": {
        "en": "Founded over 1,000 years ago, Vernazza was the wealthiest and most important village in Cinque Terre during medieval times. The Doria Castle tower still stands guard over the harbor, while the main piazza opens directly onto the tiny natural port. Unlike other villages, Vernazza has no car access at all—everything arrives by train, boat, or foot. This isolation has preserved its timeless beauty."
      }
    },
