      "title": {
        "en": "Capturing the Perfect Shot"
      },
      "subtitle": {
        "en": "Where to find the best views of Vernazza"
      },
      "content": {
        "en": "The classic Vernazza photograph is taken from the Blue Trail between Monterosso and Vernazza, about 20 minutes above the village. For harbor shots, climb to the Doria Castle or position yourself at the breakwater at sunset. Early morning offers soft light and empty streets. The church and tower create perfect compositions from multiple angles—experiment with the narrow streets as natural frames."
      },
      "testimonial": {
        "quote": {
          "en": "I've photographed villages all over Italy, but Vernazza at golden hour is something special. The way the light hits the pastel buildings and reflects off the harbor is pure magic."
        },
        "author": {
          "en": "Elena Rossi"
        },
        "role": {
          "en": "Travel Photographer"
        },
